+  const summaryLines = [];
+  summaryLines.push("Dataset ds001_nsclc contains 50,000 NSCLC patient records with no missing values and `pfs_months` as the continuous outcome.");
+  summaryLines.push(`Mean PFS was ${fmtNumber(profile.pfs.mean)} months, with observed values from ${fmtNumber(profile.pfs.min)} to ${fmtNumber(profile.pfs.max)} months. I used OLS models for adjusted signed effects on the natural month scale, plus Welch mean-difference checks for selected subgroups.`);
+  summaryLines.push("");
+  summaryLines.push("The clearest baseline prognostic signals were adverse stage, disease burden, and performance/nutrition/inflammation markers. In adjusted models, `stage_iv` and `has_brain_mets` were associated with shorter PFS, `ecog_ps` worsened PFS per point, and higher `albumin_g_dl` improved PFS. Higher `crp_mg_l` and `nlr` were both adverse. Additional metastatic-site analyses supported lower PFS with `liver_mets`, `bone_mets`, `pleural_effusion`, and `contralateral_lung_mets` when those terms were added to the broad model.");
+  summaryLines.push("");
+  summaryLines.push("Biomarker-treatment heterogeneity was strong and clinically coherent. `treatment_pembrolizumab` benefit increased with higher `pdl1_tps` and was larger in `tmb_high` patients, while `stk11_mutation` significantly attenuated pembrolizumab-associated PFS. `treatment_sotorasib` showed a large positive interaction with `kras_g12c`, and `stk11_mutation` also reduced sotorasib-associated benefit. `treatment_olaparib` showed a strong positive interaction with `brca2_mutation`. `treatment_osimertinib` showed a strong positive interaction with `egfr_mutation`; the exploratory interaction with `has_brain_mets` was tested as a possible modifier of benefit.");
+  summaryLines.push("");
+  summaryLines.push("Several biologically plausible negative-control or off-target hypotheses were not supported. Osimertinib did not show a meaningful ALK-fusion-specific benefit, and exploratory off-target interactions of sotorasib with `met_exon14_skipping`, olaparib with `her2_amplification`, and osimertinib with `ros1_fusion` were not significant or were much smaller than the matched biomarker-drug interactions.");
