+  summaryLines.push("");
+  summaryLines.push("Overall, the cohort shows a mixture of general disease-severity prognostic effects and highly specific treatment-biomarker interactions. The strongest supported predictive patterns are pembrolizumab with PD-L1/TMB and STK11 resistance, sotorasib with KRAS G12C and STK11 attenuation, olaparib with BRCA2 mutation, and osimertinib with EGFR mutation. These are observational associations from EHR-derived data, so they should be interpreted as adjusted statistical patterns rather than causal treatment effects.");
